Step 1: Determine the Owner’s Equity at the beginning and at the end from the balance sheet.  
• Beginning Owner’s Equity = 16,000,000.00  
• Ending Owner’s Equity = 16,112,375.10  

Step 2: Compute the Average Owner’s Equity.  
 Average Owner’s Equity = (Beginning Owner’s Equity + Ending Owner’s Equity) / 2  
  = (16,000,000.00 + 16,112,375.10) / 2  
  = 32,112,375.10 / 2  
  = 16,056,187.55  

Step 3: Get the Net Profit from the income statement.  
• Net Profit = 112,375.10  

Step 4: Calculate ROE using the formula:  
 ROE = Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity  
  = 112,375.10 / 16,056,187.55  
  ≈ 0.006994 or about 0.70% (when multiplied by 100 for percentage)

Thus, the Return on Equity (ROE) is approximately 0.70%.

Final Answer:

  }
